<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idd1034404-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e" identifier="/us/usc/t50/s857"><num value="857">§ 857.</num><heading> Compliance with other registration statutes</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Compliance with the registration provisions of this subchapter does not relieve any person from compliance with any other applicable registration statute.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idd1034405-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e">(<ref href="/us/act/1956-08-01/ch849/s8">Aug. 1, 1956, ch. 849, § 8</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/70/900">70 Stat. 900</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idd1034406-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idd1034407-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="idd1034408-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section was not enacted as part of the Internal Security Act of 1950 which comprises subchapters I to III of this chapter.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
